  <h2 id="the-model">The Model Behind the Site</h2>
  <p>BitcoinCycle.io is built on a single, verifiable premise: <strong>Bitcoin's market cycles are not random — they are structural and approximately time-consistent.</strong></p>
  <p>The <strong>1064/364 model</strong> is our core analytical framework. It divides every Bitcoin cycle into two phases:</p>
  <ul style="margin:0 0 16px 20px;color:var(--muted2);font-size:0.88rem;">
    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--green);">Expansion (1,064 days):</strong> The bull market phase, running from a verified cycle bottom to the next all-time high.</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:8px;"><strong style="color:var(--red);">Compression (364 days):</strong> The bear market phase, running from the ATH to the subsequent cycle bottom.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Anchored to the <strong>November 21, 2022 FTX capitulation bottom</strong> — the most structurally significant low in Bitcoin's recent history — the model generates a deterministic schedule of predicted ATH and ATL dates extending through 2050.</p>
  <p>We believe in showing our methodology openly. The formula is simple: <code style="background:var(--bg3);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--orange);">Next ATH = ATL + 1064 days</code>. No black boxes. No proprietary signals.</p>

